original: Ekström, Gustaf Natanael, kyrkoherde, Fiskebäckskil, f. 29/6/79 i Göteborg. G. 24 m. Hilda Hans’son. Barn: Gustaf Emil f. 28, d. 29. — Stud:ex. i Gbg 98, teol. fil. ex. 01, teor. teol. ex. 04, prästex. 05, prästv. 05. Paist:adj. i Länghem 05-08, v. kommin. i Gbg 08, v. pastor i Marstrand 08-10, i Lysekil 10-11, i Hishult 11-12, kyrkoadj. i Halms’tad 12-17, kommin. i Skaftö 17-24, kyrkoh. där fr. 24. Ordf. i kyrkofullm., skolråd m. m.
translated: Ekström, Gustaf Natanael, clergyman, Fiskebäckskil, born on June 29th, 1879 in Gothenburg. Married on June 24th to Hilda Hans'son. Children: Gustaf Emil born in 1928, died in 1929. He received a B.A. degree from Gothenburg in 1898, a degree in philosophy from theology in 1901, a degree in theoretical theology in 1904, and became ordained as a priest in 1905. He served as an assistant pastor in Länghem from 1905 to 1908, assistant minister in Gothenburg from 1908 to 1910, assistant pastor in Marstrand from 1908 to 1910, in Lysekil from 1910 to 1911, in Hishult from 1911 to 1912, church assistant in Halmstad from 1912 to 1917, curate in Skaftö from 1917 to 1924, and was appointed rector there from 1924. He served as chairman of the church council, school board, and more.
